Woah! That was a great scare!

Sims who love outdoors will find the fresh air and beautiful scenery of the forest rejuvenating.
It's like connect the dots... with stars.
Nothing like the smell of clean forest air!

Awesome story! That story will be told for generations to come!
Insects have so many legs, and compound eyes, and antennae....
Some of the best stories are entertaining AND provide good, moral inspiration.
Nature's bounty is the canvas of Mother Nature. What a wondrous and inspiring sight!

Listened to a story that made believers out of every Sim in the audience.
Wow. That was terrible. An ending this bad shouldn't have started in the first place.
A little dirty, but so is everything out here.
A hike can really help clear a Sim's head and bring back some focus.
Whatever that thing was, {0.SimFirstName} hopes to never see it again.
You can never be too careful when exploring mausoleums and bramble patches.

Cozying up near a campfire is such a warm and wonderful feeling.
Nothing better than golden-brown, perfectly toasted marshmallows!

That deodorant remedy will ward off the stink for a while.
Gross! What's it going to take to wash this substance off?
Gross! That sure didn't go down well...
That energizing remedy really puts a pep in your step!
That Insect Repellent will keep those pests away!
Nothing enables more focus than the sound of the game.
It's never too late to get back on the horseshoe band wagon!
Easy to Learn, Easy to master... wheres the challenge?
Congratulations! You are an epic Horseshoe Champion! Feel the glory!
Nice scare — anyone else feel goosebumps?
Gah! It won't be easy sleeping tonight!
Tents are rather flammable - being in one that's on fire is not advised.
Sometimes, an itch is so bad that taking off one's skin sounds like a reasonable solution.
This itch will simply not let up. It is unapologetic, unrepentant, unrelenting.
A quick getaway might help relieve the tension of work
Taking a day off could be the answer to the building stress of work.
Getting away from the grind is the only way to find some relaxation. Need a vacation badly!
Reading an entertaining book can put everything in perspective.
Nothing relieves stress like some time in the great outdoors!
The ferocious roar of a bear has unnerved {0.SimFirstName}.
They came, they ate, they roasted marshmallows.
Looking at the vast sky brings inspiration that anything is possible.
Woah! That was an unexpectedly spooky story!
Listened to a satisfying story that brought goosebumps
Fantastic story! Sims love an epic tale told with such detail.
Art lovers appreciate the scenic views of waterfall and cliffs.
The sounds of nature are soothing to a Good Sim
It's amazing how inspiring nature is to a creative Sim.
A story that adventurous brings out a bold streak in even the most cowardly Sim.
A story that exciting stimulates a streak of energy in any Sim!
A story that good produces a spark of inspiration!
Hearing a story that amusing provokes an ear to ear grin on any Sim!
That story will be told for years to come!
Mixing up an impeccable remedy sure feels good.
You can only get sights like flowing waterfalls and towering cliffs out here!
Nothing beats taking a piece of the outdoors home with you!
Sims who love the outdoors also love waking up to the sights and sounds of nature!
Ugh. There's way too much dirt out here…
Romantic Sims get a bit flirty when near the waterfall and cliffs in the forest.
Slobs feel right at home when being dirty comes naturally when camping.
Rocks, dirt, and plants are so drab. These just aren't sufficient sights for the enlightened.
Nothing beats eating food caught or harvested with one's own hands!
Sims with the Survivalist Trait REALLY enjoy roughing it and waking up outdoors.
Some Sims get the greatest comfort from roughin' it!
All natural ingredients are healthy and help bring balance to the circle of life.
Listened to an epic tale of adventure.
Defeating a bear in a fight is something anyone should be proud of.
Looking at the vast sky brings inspiration that anything is possible.
Nothing like the smell of clean forest air!
Back from a hike but enough energy to do ten more!
If you get really close it smells like the fresh air in an alpine forest. Mmmm... piney.
All natural stone from Granite Falls is imported and smashed together to make this stylish foundation.
Boasting compostable scented sawdust, a rainwater recycling system, and hand-carved toilet seats, the Trusty Rustic is here to answer all pressing calls of nature.
Be lulled to sleep by the smell of all natural synthetic rubber with AirKushn's inflatable double bed! Our patented rubber is guaranteed to smell like rubber for years to come.
Do you love the feeling of ticks tingling on your legs or cramped, constrained spaces? If yes, buy a sleeping bag. Otherwise, buy a Glamping Vunderbed!
Enjoy the brissily pine tree feel and the musky dirt smell without ever leaving your bed. It's not quite the forest floor, but it's close!
Prefer to keep the smell of our natural synthetic rubber all to yourself? The AirKushn inflatable single bed is coated with enough rubber to satisfy even the most hard-pressed wilderness campers.
Assembled by robots in our sleep-tech facility, the Gordian Cot marries convenience and style without compromising the discomfort of camping in the wild.
By: The Hermit of Granite Falls\n\nOkay. Time to take off the kids gloves and brew some remedies that will magically cure any ailment.
By: Harold Patterson\n\nTired of purchasing expensive medicine and sprays to remedy what ails you? Learn the ins and outs of creating your own!
By: Michael Wash\n\nMove beyond the basics of the art of Herbalism. Become more successful at creating remedies that actually work!

By: Sean Walsh \n\nWorld-renowned insect and fiction connoisseur, Sean Walsh, takes us toward the adventures of a brave Sim and her crew in a remote region of the globe where lays a land long forgotten, where giant insects reign supreme. With the Giant Mantis holding the title of King of the Jungle, will the Sim and her crew be able to join with the native ants, beetles, and butterflies to fight off the mantis threat and avoid global destruction?

By: Mike Jeffress \n\nTo behold the splendor of the Sequoia Falls is to gaze upon the greatest beauty that nature has to offer. Or is it? Learn about the fascinating true story of a Sim who succeeded against all odds through the eyes of Mike Jeffress. The story of a Sim who refused to take no for an answer. A Sim that just wouldn't quit. A Sim that created, and now operates, the world's grandest man made waterfall.

By: PJ Ranches \n\nPJ Ranches comes forth with the gripping first installment of the Ranches Family series. A young Sim girl ventured into the wilderness alone on a night the moon forgot to shine. No one knows why she left. No one knows why she never returned. What they do know is that on some nights the moon again forgets to shine, and when it does, terrible things occur. The Ranches family has come to Granite Falls looking for a break from the pains of the modern world, but their pain has only just begun...
The Night the Moon Forgot to Shine
This traditional rock ring will keep your fire contained during your trip to the great outdoors.
This chess table was made 100% out of fresh wood. Have fun and build logic, knowing that it is completely organic. No animals were harmed to create this fine piece!
Unlock this item by completing a Gold tier Weenie Roast.
Unlocked by completing a Gold tier Weenie Roast.
An exotic fish only found in rare mountainous regions. Beware their spines, they can do serious damage!
These huge marble eyed fish are color blind. They cannot see blue or yellow. Good eatin’ though.
Kin to Walleyes. Best known for their black tiger stripes and growling when they’re hungry.
Take pride in mounting a rare Mountain Lionfish!
The Walleye, decoratively displayed for every Sim's enjoyment.
Why someone would want to mount this common fish is anyone's guess.
The Blue Crawdad on a mount. He looks like a mini-lobster!
This mounted Red Crawdad is ready for display in Sim's collections of fish and other swimming things.
The mysterious blue crawdad is rumored to received its color from an industrial blueberry accident.
Kissing cousins to lobsters. But don’t tell them that, they want to be unique.
Busy as a bee. Bees are the hardest workers in the insect world. Fact: Plants rely on bees to reproduce.
These blue winged fliers are one of the largest butterflies in the world. They often rest on forest floors and hide from predators.
This butterfly cannot be mistaken due to its bright colors and unique wing design. These colors serve as a warning to predators because it is quite toxic to eat.
One of the most beautiful and majestic butterflies but they start their lives as much less attractive caterpillars. They flap their wings about 300 to 700 times a minute.
Dragonflies are said to be the first flying insects some 300 million years ago. They are expert fliers and can fly up, down and hover like a helicopter.
An ultra rare insect can be found in forests. They have been seen breathing fire. Better not get too close or lose an eyebrow!
Watch out for these little guys. They can deliver a powerful sting and love to use it. Their mounds can reach 40 cm. high and can be as deep as 5 meters.
Nothing is more magical than a firefly at night. These bioluminescent critters create their own light through chemical reactions in their bodies.
The more exotic firefly. These insects shine bright with a variety of colors. Turn off the lights and watch their amazing glow.
Well known for their beautiful iridescent colors. These beetles are one of the world's most collected insects.
Katydids love to sing and rub their wings together to make their sounds. Did you know that their ears are in their front legs?
Great garden helpers. These lovely critters actually prey on other bugs and can protect crops from other insects.
The bringers of catastrophic disasters. These insects swarm together in clouds that can cover 100 square kilometers and contain billions of locusts.
A very cool insect that can turn its head 180 degrees. The females are well known for eating their mates. Yikes!
These little blood suckers are considered the most deadly insects on the planet. Better keep your distance!
These beautiful moths primarily fly around at night. This is how they received their name "Luna", which means moon.
These fun critters love to hop and bounce around. They usually travel around in packs. More the merrier!
What's that smell? Stink bugs use their unpleasant odor to deter predators when squashed. Better handle them with care.
Beware these insects. They love to chew through the finest of woods. Make sure the lid is closed at all times.
These awkward insects move very slowly but their ability to blend into environment makes them masters of camouflage.
A majestical insect rumored to lead travelers astray. Their blueish ghostly glow can be seen on the darkest of nights.
This affordable cooler is guaranteed to keep your food cold and preserved during outings.
This aluminum cooler is lightweight and easy to carry but protects your edibles with its patented BRRR technology.
Made from the finest bark and maple leaves, this dresser stores your clothing amidst the best nature has to offer. It's like shoving your clothes in a tree!
This wood was made for burning.
A pan of Breakfast Scramble in progress.
A pan of Walleye Surprise, half done.
A plate of Breakfast Scramble. Fill your stomach with a nutritious and delicious scramble to start any hour of the day right.
A plate of Fruit Cobbler. Have your cobbler and eat it too.
A plate of Grilled Fruit. Naturally sweet, healthy doesn’t have to be boring.
Baked Potato. It might be simple, but this will give you energy to go through many hours of exploration. You can’t deny they are pretty good, so why not?
What? Don't judge. It has high protein content... if you close your eyes it tastes like French fries.
Anything tastes better when fried, especially fish.
If you want to show off your culinary chops, make this.

By: Michael Wash\n\nMove beyond the basics of the art of Herbalism. Become more successful at creating remedies that actually work!
A sturdy horseshoe, great for throwing.
Horseshoe pitching is a fun game, though it can be tough on the shoulder muscles. Now with the ergonomically designed Mick & Carbide pit, you can entertain your whole family in safety!
You no longer need to fear those deadly predators with those beady eyes glaring from the deep woods. Finally a product that allows you to see what's coming long before it sees you.
This lantern is like a full summer moon in the dark sky, lighting the night, and... dangling on a tree with string? Everything is better on a stick!
These elegantly crafted synthetic paper flowers lit with non-flammable light sources gracefully dangle on meticulously sculpted manufactured trees. Bring the light, with Origami Tree Luminaries.
Flawlessly executed by enthusiastic outdoor inclined youth who had no idea how to build a lamp, the Simtrest Lamp really acomplishes that "did it yourself" look all while providing a light source.
Made from real wood for its illuminating qualities, this tall campground floor lamp is designed by television wilderness expert Wolf Pytts himself.
It brings light - or as the cavemen called it - fire! Portably! The Lightbringer Portable. Now battery powered.
It brings light. It now also runs on clean-burning natural gas. The Lightbringer Vista. It's still portable.
What's better than branches? Branches on fire! Light up your cabin the fun way with this all wood lamp!
The enthusiastic outdoor inclined youth also make smaller lamps! Less wood, still crafty!
Help yourself find love in the forest! The Natural Beauty Mirror will help you look your best even in nature. Because tents weren't made just for sleeping.
Made with tender loving care, this rectangular wall mirror adds a cozy rustic look to any home.
Check out that authentic sticker. Renowned troubadour StickiMo really loves camping! And you will too, if you have StickiMo's realistically seasoned acoustic guitar!
Plucked from the forests of Granite Falls and transplanted into your garden, this Small Forest Fern is pleasing to the eye.
The deep woods of Granite Falls abound with this leafy fern.
The Forest Fern is a hardy plant, but in years of drought they lose their luster. Don't worry! A little water will fix it right up!
The official flower of Granite Falls National Park.
Pretty to look at and soft to touch, these purple flowers are practically perfect...except that they stink.
Brilliant, wild, and wonderful, these untamed blooms are sure to enhance any natural space.
Are they flowers or are they weeds?
To bee or not to bee! We recognize your dedication and hard work by presenting you with this award.
This traditional campfire pit will keep your fire contained during your trip to the great outdoors.
Purchase supplies and view camping information at the Ranger Station!
Purchase supplies and view camping information at the Ranger Station!
Enjoy the sensation of soft feet out in the wild! The artfully stencilled coyotes and shaped sequoia or whatever those trees are will not fail to remind you that you are in the Wilderness & Yonder!

Never be ambushed by wet grass again! This waterproof, space-age tarp will have you exclaiming to your peers about its woven polyethylene! New models now come in classic green, admiral blue, and calamari brown.
Using the same tools television wilderness expert Wolf Pytts used when he wrestled a Cotton River trout, you too will be inspired to eat in the wild with this all-weather bucket of utensils!
This limited edition wooden statue of Ranger Stanley Jackalope has him in his regal greeting pose - a pose friendly to Sims, but one also solemn and intimidating to most furry woodland animals.
An expedition to the wilderness is not complete without the Lincolnshire & Co. Crockery Trunk. This hand-woven beauty politely hollers of colonial extravagance.

Live off the same supplies as television survival expert Wolf Pytts did when he wrestled sustainable yellowfin tuna in the Sacamond River! This waterproof plastic box also doubles as an emergency floatation device.
Why water flowers when you can put flowers in the watering can? These flowers practically water themselves! What a brilliant idea! Why, thank you.
Made of dirt-safe, yet ultra-soft cotton, this adorable Ranger Stanley Jackalope plushie will tame even the fiercest of beasts. And children. But mostly children.
Tired of pots and pans burning up on you? Fear not, for these stainless steel pots are guaranteed to stay flame-resistant up to about 2750 °F, where it will then melt and become all gooey and hot.

Here at Half Foods' Grocery Store, we take pride in sourcing only the most bizarre yet delicious dehydrated and canned food products. From Salted Caramel Tomatoes to Popcorn Flavoured Organic Butter, we have it all!
Now available in Mild, Medium, Spicy, Extra Hot, and Ketchup.
The Bearly Gnome's natural environment is outdoors, so he'll enjoy being placed on the front lawn to greet (or annoy) the neighbors.
Bask in the cool outside night air with a delicious mug of this warm, cocoa-based beverage that's sure to bring a smile to your face.
A wonderfully crafted Ranger Stanley sculpture. Ever detail was painstakingly recreated for this carving.
Deftly carved wooden heart sculptures. These hearts can symbolize the love between two Sims.
Superbly crafted wooden shelf. Perfect for creating additional space in any room or hallway.
Take evasive action after a long day of hiking and indulge in the trappings of clean, warm water as it cascades down on you from a sun-baked solar hot bottle.
Be one with nature even while washing it off you! Perfect for those who don't love the dirt, bugs, and fireleaf quite as much as we do.
Let Ranger Stanley Jackalope's regal directionality guide the way with this prominent, all-natural wood sign that points the entrance to your wilderness retreat.
This kiosk will both endear and inform your visitors with an unsophisticated assortment of useful information and a tactile, all-weather wooden exterior.
For the times you need to alert Sims that they are approaching dangerous cliffs, odd-smelling plants, and/or odd-looking metal signs.
An ingenious device that pumps clean water from underground aquifers, coupled with a timeless hand-sculpted stone exterior that will match any outdoor wilderness furniture collection.
For those who want to wash off the beauty and enchantment of nature this is the sink for you!
The Gordian Spritz are not only known for their loud colors that match your most vivid camping fantasies, but also for attracting attention a mile away.
Take a break and go fishing. This amazing folding chair is durable and comfortable.
Unlock by completing a Silver tier Weenie Roast.
Unlocked by completing a Silver tier Weenie Roast.
Most like comfort. Others prefer style. Few desire elegance. Here at Lumber Jack's Home Furniture we like choppin' trees! Like this one that we just attached legs to for your sitting needs.
This isn't just wood, this is wood with a cushion! Forget about our competitors, this is luxury! There is nothing this chair can't do!
Lean back and relax in this charming chair crafted by the finest lumberjacks. The Timber Log Chair is unique and extremely durable. Keep away for termites though!
What's better then a rock that has been crafted into a mighty throne? Nothing! Relax while outside in this hand carved stone chair.
This rustic chair delivers comfort, durability and charm. Carved from an actual tree stump, it is naturally resistant to the elements and will deliver lasting quality.
The Basic line of Gordian foldable chairs sport a timeless, rainproof design that will not just accessorize your campsite with style, but will also allow you a place to rest your butt.
The Throne line of Gordian foldable chairs have a luxurious cotton seat padding and a full structured armrest, boasting comfort that almost threatens anyone nearby to not sit in it.
What's better for cozying up by the fire than an all wood loveseat? The Not Your Average Firewood Loveseat is made from the softest wood for extreme comfort, and it's 75% fire resistant!
Don't let its convenient simplicity fool you - this intimate dual-seater from Gordian has been voted 'Most Snugglable Foldable Chair' three years in a row by Camping Bottoms magazine.
What gets you closer to a loved one then sharing splinters in your hind quarters? A log hewn into a bench. Now, two people can be uncomfortable within reason together on this log!

After a long, hard day at work what could be better for resting your tired limbs than a tree trunk! Imported from real lumberjacks in the Andes. Don't worry, this ottoman is way more expensive than it looks!
Sleek lines and colorful cushions make this sofa a must-have for every cabin! It's so comfortable it's like napping on a tree!
This ultra sturdy coffee table will be the talk of the town! The Rockin' Coffee Table endures fires, floods, even dance parties! All you have to do is get it in your house!
Compliment your wood dining chairs with Lumber Jack's Home Furniture Coffee Table. Cause we really like choppin' trees!
When Wolf Pytts goes camping he uses the Pocket Puter Folding Table. Looks like a table, but fits in your pocket! Perfect for those mid-hike picnics!
Don't cry over spilled milk! This table is stain proof. Its granite coating gives a protective layer to this stylish end table. It's impenetrable!
A stump is not always a stump. This bit of nature was magically transformed into useful table by the finest craftsman. A perfect look for the outdoor designer.
The Pack Cube sports a neo-modernist design that stores extra camping supplies without sacrificing strength and eating surface.
Bring that rustic edge to any room with the Forest Lovers End Table. Cause if you love the forest, you need more wooden furniture!
Recreate the episode of 'Pytts vs The River' where television wilderness expert Wolf Pytts celebrates his forty-third wrestled tuna of the day by playing card games with his friends.
The Pack Cube: Orthotope Edition is like the original Pack Cube, but longer! A result of clever engineering, this Pack Cube will provide twice the eating surface without costing twice as much.
It's a picnic table! It's a purse! No, it's Super Picnic Purse! Now your favorite picnic table folds into the perfect accessory! Style and utility in one!
The Picnicer is expertly crafted by our in house stone mason and woodland creatures for the ultimate picnic experience.
Have you ever wanted to enjoy the simplistic elegance and comfort of a picnic table in your own home? Well now you can! Perfect for things like indoor barbecues, indoor picnics, and indoor parks.
The Cabin-in-a-Bag lets you bring all the comforts of home to a campsite. This large tent will easily accommodate you, your friends, and possibly a grizzly bear.
The Easy Camper is a small, sleek, and easy-to-assemble tent that makes roughing it feel not so rough at all.

Who doesn't like rummaging through trash for a yummy meal? Well now you can rummage to your heart's desire all while avoiding that nasty smell. The Odor Killer gives your trash that fresh flowery scent. Looks like trash, smells like an angel!
This pine tree is pining for water. So dry, so sad...
Not too short, not too tall, this tree is the most popular pine varietal found in the forests of Granite Falls.
A favorite of woodpeckers and squirrels, this small pine is native to the verdant forests of Granite Falls.
Hawthorn trees are not only lovely, but sturdy and strong too. All hail the Mighty Hawthorn Tree, king of the forest!
Guaranteed to be a conversation starter at your next garden party, this twisted oak is a unique addition to any yard.
This tall pine is native to the verdant forests of Granite Falls. When this tree falls in the forest you can bet it makes a lot of noise...

There are five species of fish unique to Granite Falls. Try not to over-fish our streams, though!
If you need to purchase supplies, like a tent or cooler, go to the Ranger Station in the camp ground.
You can collect herbs in Granite Falls and use a grill or stove to make remedies with them. I hear the deodorant is popular.
There's a public restroom in the camp ground for your potty breaks and hygiene needs. It’s a popular hangout for insects. I warned you!
You may want to bring a cooler with you when hiking in the woods. No telling how long you'll be out and about. You might get hungry!
We keep hearing rumors of a Hermit somewhere in the National Park. I think it's hogwash, myself.
We've had a good number of bear sightings recently. Be careful out there!
There are so many creepy crawly insects to collect in Granite Falls. Be on the lookout!
Invite a Sim to join you on vacation.
Thanks for ordering! The items {0.SimFirstName} purchased can be found in {M0.his}{F0.her} inventory.

{0.SimFirstName} feels {M0.he}{F0.she} is on the verge of finding something special, something to make this all worth it, but is quickly tiring. Should {0.SimFirstName} take a quick nap or sally forth?
{0.SimFirstName} marches through the brush in high spirits swinging arms and singing songs when a shiny object catches the eye. Ah, temptation.
After making the choice of cowardice most foul, {0.SimFirstName}'s exploration ended where it started. The brambles are not greener on this side.
After several minutes of hacking furiously through the brush, a large web is blocking {0.SimFirstName}'s way. One would prefer that web is not paired with a Spider…
{0.SimFirstName} has navigated the nigh foiling foliage to discover a sacred cove in the midst of the forest. A cove containing a mysterious Sim…
With toes dipped in the cool brook and a line cast in the water, {0.SimFirstName} encountered one of nature's most fearsome fishing enthusiasts…Ursus Arctos!
A semi-rational fear of enormously industrious spiders sent {0.SimFirstName} to find an alternate route. Naturally, this route was coated in over-ripe fireleaf!
The herbicide seems to have cleared a path, though it looks like the bramble is already growing back. {0.SimFirstName} sees a crazy looking Sim in the distance...
Surrounded by thicket, thorns and danger most assuredly, {0.SimFirstName} is left with only one decision: Step Forward or Retreat from Adventure.
It appears {0.SimFirstName} has some herbicide on hand. That would certainly clear up this bramble mess!
After waking from a nightmare about a never ending itch, {0.SimFirstName} realizes it was no dream! One must look closely for ticks before sleep.
As {0.SimFirstName} pushes through the foliage with intrepid courage, a bubbling brook emerges. Should {0.SimFirstName} stop to fish?
As {0.SimFirstName} reaches for the shiny, succulent treasure, more shiny treasures…things…blink in. Gulp! The shine was not that of a jewel, but of a woodland monster!

Having trouble getting through the Bramble Patch? Then it's concocting time! Start with a dash of Herbalism skill, throw in a select couple of ingredients, and voila! You now have yourself your very own, homemade Herbicide!
If you enjoy slimy things and getting up excessively early, then why not try your hand at some fishing while you're here? You might even get your hook into the elusive Mountain Lionfish!

Kick back, take a load off, relax. Rest your head on the soft grass and gaze into the heavens, taking in the wondrous sights of the stars and clouds above. Or don't. Whatever. I don't care. I'm just a sign.

Have you located the thorny Bramble Patch? No Sim has been brave enough to venture forth to the other side yet. Which simply must mean there are incredible secrets to uncover over yonder! Now get a move on and unravel those mysteries!
I hope you remembered to pack your trusty tent, cooler, and grilling ingredients. If not, do not fret! The Ranger Station can provide you with any of your camping needs. All you have to do is ask!

Everyone loves hot dogs! Throw a Weenie Roast Event to gather your crew around the campfire for a taste of these delicious morsels. Impress your fellow campers enough and you might even earn a fabulous prize!
Need to change outfits? Change in your tent! Fashion yourself a nice camping outfit and return to the great outdoors!
Horsehoes! Good for playing horseshoes with your best pals or closest family. Just don't try wearing them on your feet. For then, of course, you will feel remorse because you are not a horse.
Campfire sing-a-longs are a long standing tradition amongst campers. It's just too bad tradition does not equate to quality vocalists. Keep at it and one day you might lead a passable sing-a-long!
Having bear problems? Why not befriend the rascally prankster?

Be careful to inspect every overgrown path and bountiful glade of the forest to make sure you don't miss a thing. You never know what unique collectibles you might find. There are even rumors of a strange, old Sim who lives beyond the deep forest!

Whether you're feeling adventurous or looking for some relaxation, Granite Falls has it all! Explore the deep forest or lounge around the campground, it's your choice. The only requirement is that you have a good time!

Sick of all those trees everywhere? Gather around the campfire to get some revenge on that wood while telling stories to your fellow campers. Wait until night and you may be able to frighten some of the children with Ghost Stories!

The many plants and herbs of Granite Falls lend themselves well to the art of Herbalism. These remedies are generally meant to do good, but they don't always have to be. Why not try mixing up a Fireleaf Extract and applying it to a rival's tent?
Telling Ghost Stories is at the heart of any good night of camping, but be careful in their telling. Get carried away and you may find yourself attracting an uninvited guest!

Crawdads are common in the waters around Granite Falls, but the true angler will be on the lookout for the rare Blue Crawdad. Read on for fishing tips and tricks from Wilderness Digest’s own Angler Bob!
Don't miss an exclusive interview with Ranger Boyd! He shares his experiences, and secrets, with the rare Will-o-the-Wisp that is found deep in the woods of Granite Falls.

The Walleye Surprise is a great camping recipe! If you have a high cooking skill, you can make this. Ingredients require a Walleye, some Huckleberry, and Locust. You may become Inspired from cooking it!
Eat something bad? Try making a Tummy Therapy. Ingredients: Huckleberry, Sage, and Termite
Soothing Skin Balm can be used to get rid of the itchies! Make it using Chamomile, Basil, and Locust.
Remember: even when you're away from home, you can still die. Make sure you have all the essentials, or make them with things you find out in the wilderness!
Vacations are a great way to relieve stress and relax. Take some Paid Time Off work to ensure that bills are covered while you're away.
Franks and Beans are one of the most common things to eat while camping. But be careful! These things cause gas!
Sightings of the mysterious Sim living in the Deep Woods! Anonymous Sims have said to have learned secret recipes from this mysterious master of Herbalism.
Insects may seem yucky, but strange and unusual ones can be found in the Deep Woods. Catching the Rainbow Firefly would not only give you bragging rights, but you could sell it for lots of Simoleons!

Deodorant is a must for any hiker, and we here at Wilderness Digest will tell you how to craft our favorite blend from berries and fresh herbs! Elderberry, Strawberry, and a touch of Parsley make a heavenly body spray that hides even the foulest of odors.

Wild plants grow all over the campgrounds and in the forest of Granite Falls. But be careful! Some plants are toxic and can have negative effects on Sims. Sims with high Herbalism skill will be able to identify toxic plants versus non-toxic plants.\n\nPlants can also be eaten or used to make herbal remedies.

Sims can brew herbal remedies on grills or stoves. Before brewing, plants must be identified before they can be used in an herbal remedy recipe. Once a Sim has identified all ingredients required for a specific herbal remedy, they’ll be able to brew it. As Sims level up their Herbalism skill, they’ll be able to make better remedies with longer-lasting effects.
The Herbalism skill allows your Sims to identify wild plants and brew potent herbal remedies.\n\nSims gain the Herbalism skill by Identifying wild plants and brewing remedies.
You can visit other Sims and explore the world while being on Vacation! There's a lot of things to discover in each world and you only have a limited time...that is unless you extend your stay.
Every Sim needs a Vacation from time to time! Sims can use the phone or computer to book a Vacation.

When booking a Vacation, specify the amount of time you want it to last as well as the Lot you want your Sims to stay in. You can also invite your friends to join your Sim, just remember that the Active Household will pay for the Vacation.
When your Vacation days run out, you can choose whether or not to extend the Vacation. Just remember that the current Active Household pays for the extension.
